"n.荷尔蒙，激素 【记】 horm(鼓动，冲动)+on e→激素; 【同】 参考：horme(有目的 活动的驱动力) n. 荷尔蒙(经由血液循环到达另一组织来影响生理活动, 例如生长或新陈代谢); 激素(调节生长之功能的物质) 【记】horm冲动, 兴奋－荷尔蒙 【参】horme(n 有目的之行动) 【记】音：荷尔蒙 hormone (n.)  1905, from Greek hormon ""that which sets in motion,"" present participle of horman ""impel, urge on,"" from horme ""onset, impulse,"" from PIE *or-sma-, from root *er- ""to move, set in motion."" Used by Hippocrates to denote a vital principle; modern meaning coined by English physiologist Ernest Henry Starling (1866-1927). Jung used horme (1915) in reference to hypothetical mental energy that drives unconscious activities and instincts. Related: Hormones."
